1
00:00:48,309 --> 00:00:50,006
 [THUNDER RUMBLING]

2
00:00:54,184 --> 00:00:58,536
 IOLAUS:  <i>You think you know</i>
  <i>the truth about him?</i>

3
00:00:59,450 --> 00:01:01,278
 [LIGHTNING CRASHING]

4
00:01:03,411 --> 00:01:07,067
  <i>His father was Zeus.</i>
  <i>The Zeus.</i>

5
00:01:07,110 --> 00:01:08,372
  <i>King of the gods.</i>

6
00:01:12,202 --> 00:01:16,032
  <i>His mother, Alcmene,</i>
  <i>a mortal woman.</i>

7
00:01:18,165 --> 00:01:24,171
  <i>Together, they had a boy.</i>

8
00:01:27,304 --> 00:01:29,480
  <i>But Zeus' queen, Hera,</i>

9
00:01:29,524 --> 00:01:32,440
  <i>saw this bastard child</i>
  <i>as an insult,</i>

10
00:01:32,483 --> 00:01:36,313
  <i>a living reminder</i>
  <i>of her husband's infidelity.</i>

11
00:01:36,357 --> 00:01:39,186
  <i>Alcmene named</i>
  <i>the boy Hercules,</i>

12
00:01:39,229 --> 00:01:41,449
 <i>which means</i> 
<i>"glory of Hera,"</i>

13
00:01:41,492 --> 00:01:44,800
 <i>but this failed</i> 
<i>to appease the goddess.</i>

14
00:01:44,843 --> 00:01:47,194
  <i>She wanted him dead.</i>

15
00:02:01,860 --> 00:02:02,818
[HISSING]

16
00:02:02,861 --> 00:02:05,168
 [CRUSHING]

17
00:02:05,212 --> 00:02:06,822
 [GASPS]

18
00:02:06,865 --> 00:02:09,216
  <i>Luckily,</i>
  <i>he took after his father.</i>

19
00:02:11,218 --> 00:02:13,263
 <i>Once he reached manhood,</i>

20
00:02:13,307 --> 00:02:16,223
  <i>the gods commanded him</i>
  <i>to perform Twelve Labors,</i>

21
00:02:16,266 --> 00:02:18,834
  <i>twelve dangerous missions.</i>

22
00:02:18,877 --> 00:02:21,532
 <i>If he completed them all</i> 
<i>and survived,</i>

23
00:02:21,576 --> 00:02:24,405
  <i>Hera agreed to finally</i>
  <i>let him live in peace.</i>

24
00:02:36,895 --> 00:02:38,332
 [ROARING]

25
00:02:43,293 --> 00:02:45,556
  <i>He fought the Lernean Hydra!</i>

26
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:53,521
[ROARING]

27
00:02:56,915 --> 00:02:59,266
 [PANTING]

28
00:02:59,309 --> 00:03:01,485
  <i>He battled</i>
  <i>the Erymanthian Boar!</i>

29
00:03:14,933 --> 00:03:18,502
  <i>But his greatest Labor</i>
  <i>was the Nemean Lion.</i>

30
00:03:18,546 --> 00:03:20,156
[LION GROWLING]

31
00:03:23,551 --> 00:03:25,683
  <i>This was no ordinary beast.</i>

32
00:03:27,424 --> 00:03:29,339
 [ROARS]

33
00:03:29,383 --> 00:03:32,473
 <i>It had a hide so tough, no</i> 
<i>weapon could penetrate it.</i>

34
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,431
[ROARING LOUDLY]

35
00:03:45,442 --> 00:03:49,185
 <i>But even this monster was no</i> 
<i>match for the son of Zeus.</i>

36
00:03:52,928 --> 00:03:54,538
 What a load of crap!

37
00:03:54,582 --> 00:03:56,279
Every word is true.

38
00:03:56,323 --> 00:03:57,411
 [MEN LAUGHING]

39
00:03:59,326 --> 00:04:00,414
 [IOLAUS WHIMPERS]

40
00:04:00,457 --> 00:04:01,719
 GRYZA:
 You know what I think?

41
00:04:01,763 --> 00:04:04,287
 This friend of yours
 doesn't even exist.

42
00:04:04,331 --> 00:04:05,419
 [MEN CONTINUE LAUGHING]

43
00:04:05,462 --> 00:04:08,204
 Laugh all you want.
 He's coming.

44
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:10,511
 And be warned, Gryza,
 he despises pirates.

45
00:04:11,512 --> 00:04:13,514
Macedonia has been
good to us.

46
00:04:13,557 --> 00:04:16,299
 Plenty of villages
 ripe for pillaging.

47
00:04:16,343 --> 00:04:18,258
 We are here to stay.

48
00:04:18,301 --> 00:04:19,476
 Finish him.

49
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:22,566
 [GASPING]

50
00:04:22,610 --> 00:04:25,308
 The more you struggle,
 the faster you drop.

51
00:04:25,352 --> 00:04:26,527
 [GRYZA CHUCKLES]

52
00:04:26,570 --> 00:04:28,616
 Indeed, your fleet
 is strong. I...

53
00:04:32,663 --> 00:04:35,275
 Yet, as I was
 about to explain

54
00:04:35,318 --> 00:04:37,625
 before I was
 so rudely interrupted,

55
00:04:37,668 --> 00:04:39,540
the Nemean Lion
was strong, too.

56
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:42,630
Yet, he still destroyed it.

57
00:04:42,673 --> 00:04:46,373
 And not with a sword
 or a spear or arrows. No!

58
00:04:50,420 --> 00:04:52,292
 I did it with my bare hands!

59
00:04:55,643 --> 00:04:56,731
 Or so they say.

60
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,736
 Hercules.

61
00:05:01,779 --> 00:05:03,651
 Is this all the men
 you have?

62
00:05:03,694 --> 00:05:06,958
 There's forty of us.
 One of you.

63
00:05:07,002 --> 00:05:08,960
 The king of this land
 has offered me gold

64
00:05:09,004 --> 00:05:10,614
to dispose of you.

65
00:05:10,658 --> 00:05:13,487
So leave or die.

66
00:05:13,530 --> 00:05:15,315
 I get paid either way.

67
00:05:16,359 --> 00:05:18,405
 Make him bleed.

68
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,798
 [MEN YELLING]

69
00:05:25,412 --> 00:05:27,675
 Five men with a single blow.

70
00:05:27,718 --> 00:05:30,373
 Still think you can destroy
 the son of Zeus?

71
00:05:30,417 --> 00:05:32,419
Bring me his head!

72
00:05:32,462 --> 00:05:33,550
 [MEN YELLING]

73
00:05:35,465 --> 00:05:37,511
 Seems they need more
 convincing, Autolycus.

74
00:05:37,554 --> 00:05:38,686
 That's why we're here.

75
00:05:40,078 --> 00:05:41,036
 [MEN SCREAM]

76
00:05:41,079 --> 00:05:42,385
 Atalanta.

77
00:05:42,429 --> 00:05:43,430
 [GROANS]

78
00:05:46,084 --> 00:05:47,434
 Amphiaraus.

79
00:05:50,045 --> 00:05:51,525
 May Zeus forgive you.

80
00:05:51,568 --> 00:05:52,656
 Tydeus? [YELLING]

81
00:05:54,397 --> 00:05:55,572
 [ALL GRUNTING]

82
00:05:58,401 --> 00:05:59,750
[MEN SCREAMING]

83
00:06:16,419 --> 00:06:18,421
 Die, Hercules!

84
00:06:18,465 --> 00:06:19,422
 [SCREAMING STOPS]

85
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,646
 Ah, good man.
 [CHUCKLES]

86
00:06:26,124 --> 00:06:27,691
 [PANTING]

87
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,742
 [ROPE SNAPPING]

88
00:06:35,786 --> 00:06:37,397
Hurry!

89
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:38,746
 Hurry! Uncle!

90
00:06:38,789 --> 00:06:40,704
 [YELPING]

91
00:06:40,748 --> 00:06:42,053
Uncle, hurry!

92
00:06:42,097 --> 00:06:43,664
Hurry! Hurry!

93
00:06:46,144 --> 00:06:47,581
[SCREAMS]

94
00:06:47,624 --> 00:06:49,583
 Any longer, Uncle...

95
00:06:49,626 --> 00:06:52,499
And the girls would finally
be safe from your attentions.

96
00:06:56,590 --> 00:06:58,113
 The rest of you may go.

97
00:06:59,462 --> 00:07:00,507
 But not you.

98
00:07:12,780 --> 00:07:14,738
 AUTOLYCUS: Thirteen,

99
00:07:14,782 --> 00:07:18,438
 fourteen, fifteen, sixteen,

100
00:07:18,481 --> 00:07:20,091
 seventeen... That was fun.

101
00:07:20,135 --> 00:07:22,746
...eighteen,
nineteen, twenty.

102
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:25,880
 Twenty pirates
 at two gold pieces a head,

103
00:07:25,923 --> 00:07:28,448
 minus the headless ones.
 Let's see.

104
00:07:28,491 --> 00:07:29,623
 Not a bad night.

105
00:07:29,666 --> 00:07:31,494
 You see how the pirates ran?

106
00:07:31,538 --> 00:07:33,148
 My story
 softened their resolve.

107
00:07:33,191 --> 00:07:35,759
Their resolve
must be broken, Iolaus.

108
00:07:35,803 --> 00:07:37,500
 When you spread
 the legend of Hercules,

109
00:07:37,544 --> 00:07:39,676
 make it bigger, scarier.

110
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:42,766
The more they believe Hercules
is truly the son of Zeus,

111
00:07:42,810 --> 00:07:43,941
 the less likely
 they are to fight.

112
00:07:44,812 --> 00:07:45,813
 Oh!

113
00:07:47,554 --> 00:07:48,555
 Aye.

114
00:07:50,557 --> 00:07:51,688
Amphiaraus? Mmm?

115
00:07:52,384 --> 00:07:53,864
Care to join us
here on Earth?

116
00:07:59,522 --> 00:08:01,655
 A lion and a crow
 in strange alliance,

117
00:08:01,698 --> 00:08:03,874
 fighting across
 a sea of corpses.

118
00:08:10,577 --> 00:08:12,535
 If you're going to use
 those herbs, Amphiaraus,

119
00:08:12,579 --> 00:08:13,754
 at least share.

120
00:08:14,232 --> 00:08:14,929
 Huh?

121
00:08:15,712 --> 00:08:17,584
[ALL CHUCKLING]

122
00:08:18,585 --> 00:08:19,542
 [UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:08:19,586 --> 00:08:20,630
 [INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

124
00:08:20,674 --> 00:08:25,200
 Hold it!
 Hold it! Hold it!

125
00:08:28,595 --> 00:08:30,553
Keep practicing, boys!

126
00:08:30,597 --> 00:08:31,554
 So, who's next?
 You? You?

127
00:08:31,598 --> 00:08:32,773
 [SNIFFING]

128
00:08:32,816 --> 00:08:33,861
 Ah!

129
00:08:36,603 --> 00:08:38,169
 That's a pretty sight.

130
00:08:38,213 --> 00:08:40,737
 One more payday, Autolycus,
 that's all we need.

131
00:08:40,781 --> 00:08:43,566
 Then we get to live
 like the kings we've served.

132
00:08:43,610 --> 00:08:45,742
 Or live simply.

133
00:08:47,744 --> 00:08:50,530
You still dreaming
of barbarian lands?

134
00:08:50,573 --> 00:08:52,183
 Beyond the Aegean.

135
00:08:52,227 --> 00:08:53,576
 At the shores
 of the Black Sea.

136
00:08:53,620 --> 00:08:55,230
That is where
I will live out

137
00:08:55,273 --> 00:08:56,884
 the rest of my days
 in solitude.

138
00:08:56,927 --> 00:08:58,886
 Boring, if you ask me.

139
00:08:58,929 --> 00:09:00,714
 Maybe so, Autolycus.

140
00:09:00,757 --> 00:09:02,019
 But I'll never find peace

141
00:09:02,063 --> 00:09:03,891
 unless I move
 as far away as possible.

142
00:09:05,588 --> 00:09:06,850
What of Tydeus?

143
00:09:06,894 --> 00:09:08,635
Without you
to temper his rage,

144
00:09:08,678 --> 00:09:09,853
 I fear what he may become.

145
00:09:09,897 --> 00:09:11,899
 Tydeus will go with me.

146
00:09:11,942 --> 00:09:14,728
 Civilization has become
 too civilized for us.

147
00:09:14,771 --> 00:09:15,816
 Uncle!

148
00:09:17,295 --> 00:09:19,950
 Join us. The girls
 are eager to welcome you.

149
00:09:28,916 --> 00:09:30,961
 See? I told you
 I knew Hercules.

150
00:09:32,789 --> 00:09:34,269
 Are you his servant?

151
00:09:34,312 --> 00:09:35,792
I'm his nephew.

152
00:09:35,836 --> 00:09:37,228
 Are you really?

153
00:09:37,272 --> 00:09:39,274
I tell of Hercules'
Twelve Labors,

154
00:09:39,317 --> 00:09:42,016
 like the Nemean Lion,
 the Apples of Hesperides,

155
00:09:42,059 --> 00:09:44,888
 the Belt of Hippolyta
 with its buxom naked Amazons

156
00:09:44,932 --> 00:09:46,803
 and exciting bondage.
 I immortalize...

157
00:09:46,847 --> 00:09:49,763
He talks,
while the rest of us fight.

158
00:09:49,806 --> 00:09:52,243
It is a wonder you share
the same blood as Hercules.

159
00:09:52,287 --> 00:09:53,070
 [WOMEN LAUGHING]

160
00:09:53,984 --> 00:09:54,985
 Have fun.

161
00:09:55,507 --> 00:09:56,944
 Ladies. BOTH: Oh...

162
00:10:17,355 --> 00:10:19,053
 What do you want
 with Hercules?

163
00:10:19,096 --> 00:10:20,968
 My words are for him,
 not you.

164
00:10:21,011 --> 00:10:22,970
 HERCULES:
 Atalanta, it's all right.

165
00:10:29,803 --> 00:10:31,935
 You certainly
 are a hard man to find.

166
00:10:31,979 --> 00:10:33,981
 Maybe I don't want
 anyone to find me.

167
00:10:34,024 --> 00:10:35,983
 I'm not just anyone.

168
00:10:36,026 --> 00:10:39,290
My name is Ergenia,
daughter to Lord Cotys.

169
00:10:39,334 --> 00:10:41,858
Your father is most fortunate to
have such a beautiful heir.

170
00:10:43,904 --> 00:10:46,602
 My father
 is most unfortunate.

171
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:48,996
 He battles a warlord.
 Rhesus.

172
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:51,085
 Our land is torn
 by civil war.

173
00:10:51,128 --> 00:10:52,695
 Every day villages
 are destroyed,

174
00:10:52,739 --> 00:10:54,610
 crops ruined,
 innocents slaughtered.

175
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:55,872
We all have problems.

176
00:10:57,134 --> 00:11:00,007
 Well, perhaps
 I can convince you

177
00:11:00,050 --> 00:11:01,791
 to make our problems
 your own.

178
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:05,708
Unfortunately, my lady,
Hercules is fully committed

179
00:11:05,752 --> 00:11:07,710
till the Feast of Dionysus.

180
00:11:07,754 --> 00:11:09,973
We could, however, advance
you to the front of the line,

181
00:11:10,017 --> 00:11:11,758
 for the right price.

182
00:11:11,801 --> 00:11:13,063
 Hmm.

183
00:11:13,107 --> 00:11:14,891
 I thought heroes
 fight for glory.

184
00:11:14,935 --> 00:11:16,893
But mercenaries
fight for gold.

185
00:11:16,937 --> 00:11:18,765
 Lord Cotys is a rich man.

186
00:11:18,808 --> 00:11:20,114
 I like him already.

187
00:11:20,157 --> 00:11:21,376
 If you agree to aid him,

188
00:11:21,419 --> 00:11:23,770
 he will pay
 your weight in gold.

189
00:11:27,774 --> 00:11:28,949
 Eat up.

190
00:11:34,955 --> 00:11:37,044
 "A lion and crow
 in strange alliance."

191
00:11:37,784 --> 00:11:39,046
 Told you.

192
00:11:44,834 --> 00:11:46,401
Where are we going?

193
00:12:48,506 --> 00:12:50,770
It is good to see you safe,
my lady.

194
00:12:54,512 --> 00:12:56,819
This war claims
more victims every day.

195
00:12:56,863 --> 00:12:58,429
We were concerned, my lady.

196
00:12:58,473 --> 00:13:01,476
 Thank you, General Sitacles.
 I was well protected.

197
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:02,825
 Ah.

198
00:13:02,869 --> 00:13:05,872
 The mighty Hercules.
 An honor.

199
00:13:07,917 --> 00:13:13,793
But not quite as big an
honor as I expected.

200
00:13:17,884 --> 00:13:21,017
 Uncle? Hera. Impressive.

201
00:13:21,888 --> 00:13:23,106
 It's meant to be.

202
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:25,108
 It took five years
 and a thousand men

203
00:13:25,152 --> 00:13:26,849
 to build her temple.

204
00:13:26,893 --> 00:13:29,025
 Hera is the patron
 goddess of Thrace.

205
00:13:29,069 --> 00:13:30,505
 Everyone knows the legend.

206
00:13:30,548 --> 00:13:33,508
How Hera seeks
to destroy Hercules.

207
00:13:33,551 --> 00:13:36,990
 Perhaps the right cause
 might finally reconcile you.

208
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:38,513
 Mother!

209
00:13:38,556 --> 00:13:39,906
 Arius.

210
00:13:43,213 --> 00:13:44,519
You're Hercules.

211
00:13:44,562 --> 00:13:46,260
 That's right.

212
00:13:46,303 --> 00:13:48,871
My name is Arius. I know
all your Labors by heart.

213
00:13:48,915 --> 00:13:51,526
You killed the giant Geryon
with a single blow,

214
00:13:51,569 --> 00:13:53,223
 cleaned the Augean
 stables in one night.

215
00:13:53,267 --> 00:13:54,921
Hercules is probably tired.

216
00:13:54,964 --> 00:13:56,009
And the Labor of the Hide,
and the Labor of the Mares.

217
00:13:56,052 --> 00:13:57,053
 That's enough, Arius.

218
00:13:57,097 --> 00:13:58,533
 Come along. [CHUCKLES]

219
00:13:58,576 --> 00:14:00,100
 [WHISPERS]
 Stay away from him.

220
00:14:00,143 --> 00:14:03,190
 Men who deal in violence
 attract violence.

221
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:06,019
But he's Hercules. He's no mere
mortal. He's the greatest!

222
00:14:08,978 --> 00:14:10,937
 Lord Cotys will see you now.

223
00:14:18,161 --> 00:14:20,120
 Have you ever met royalty,
 Hercules?

224
00:14:20,990 --> 00:14:22,557
 Once or twice.

225
00:14:40,009 --> 00:14:41,141
 BOTH: Father! Ah! [CHUCKLES]

226
00:14:41,184 --> 00:14:42,229
[APPLAUSE]

227
00:14:46,363 --> 00:14:47,843
Megara.

228
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:52,152
 Welcome home, my love.

229
00:14:55,633 --> 00:14:56,896
 [ALL CHEERING]

230
00:14:59,159 --> 00:15:00,160
 Hercules!

231
00:15:04,164 --> 00:15:05,556
 Whenever I'm here,

232
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:07,907
 I imagine this is what
 Elysium must look like.

233
00:15:07,950 --> 00:15:10,300
 [CHUCKLES] Well,
 men like us
 have the means

234
00:15:10,344 --> 00:15:13,303
 to create our own paradise
 on Earth. Look.

235
00:15:15,044 --> 00:15:16,611
 Magnificent, aren't they?

236
00:15:18,221 --> 00:15:19,396
 Well, do not keep us
 in suspense.

237
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:22,008
Are we safe
from the monster Hydra?

238
00:15:25,011 --> 00:15:26,882
 The Hydra's heads,
 Your Majesty.

239
00:15:35,021 --> 00:15:37,023
The masks of serpents.

240
00:15:38,328 --> 00:15:41,244
 No wonder men thought
 they were monsters.

241
00:15:41,288 --> 00:15:43,203
 You've done your sovereign
 a great service. Come.

242
00:15:44,378 --> 00:15:46,989
 Let the people
 have their hero.

243
00:15:47,033 --> 00:15:51,211
 MALE SERVANT:
 All hail King Eurystheus.

244
00:15:51,254 --> 00:15:54,040
 And the mighty
 protector of Athens,

245
00:15:54,083 --> 00:15:56,172
 Hercules![CROWD CHEERING]

246
00:15:58,087 --> 00:16:01,003
 CROWD: [CHANTING]
 Hercules! Hercules!
 Hercules!

247
00:16:01,047 --> 00:16:02,309
A man faced
with such adoration

248
00:16:02,352 --> 00:16:05,094
 might be tempted
 to think himself a god.

249
00:16:07,270 --> 00:16:09,359
I only want to be
a husband and a father.

250
00:16:15,278 --> 00:16:16,323
 [BOTH SCREAMING]

251
00:16:17,715 --> 00:16:19,108
Lord Cotys awaits.

252
00:16:38,301 --> 00:16:40,173
 Hercules.

253
00:16:41,739 --> 00:16:43,176
Welcome.

254
00:16:44,220 --> 00:16:49,182
 An honor to host
 such a legend.

255
00:16:50,705 --> 00:16:54,187
 But in legend,
 you fight alone.

256
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:57,190
My reputation would not
exist without my comrades.

257
00:16:58,713 --> 00:16:59,496
 Autolycus of Sparta.

258
00:17:02,195 --> 00:17:03,979
 Tydeus of Thebes.

259
00:17:06,286 --> 00:17:07,417
 Atalanta of Scythia.

260
00:17:09,202 --> 00:17:10,986
 Iolaus of Athens.

261
00:17:11,769 --> 00:17:14,076
 And Amphiaraus of Argos.

262
00:17:14,120 --> 00:17:15,425
 Amphiaraus?

263
00:17:17,471 --> 00:17:20,387
 The famed seer of Argos.

264
00:17:20,430 --> 00:17:23,129
 It is said that you have
 glimpsed your own death,

265
00:17:23,172 --> 00:17:24,521
 so you fight each battle

266
00:17:24,565 --> 00:17:27,350
 knowing that it is not yet
 your time to die.

267
00:17:27,394 --> 00:17:29,700
 What else can you tell
 of the future?

268
00:17:29,744 --> 00:17:32,442
 Only what the gods
 see fit to reveal.

269
00:17:32,486 --> 00:17:35,358
 A shame. It would have been
 a great gift

270
00:17:35,402 --> 00:17:37,230
 to know the outcome
 of this war.

271
00:17:37,273 --> 00:17:40,755
The gods can be frustrating
sometimes, Lord Cotys.

272
00:17:40,798 --> 00:17:41,756
 [CHUCKLES]

273
00:17:45,803 --> 00:17:47,327
 [SIGHS]

274
00:17:47,370 --> 00:17:50,373
 With respect,
 I fear that the task ahead

275
00:17:50,417 --> 00:17:51,766
 might not be suitable
 for a woman,

276
00:17:52,854 --> 00:17:55,117
 even if she is
 an Amazon warrior.

277
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:04,170
 I stand corrected.

278
00:18:05,345 --> 00:18:07,129
 [INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

279
00:18:07,173 --> 00:18:09,784
 COTYS: When the kings
 of yesteryear built

280
00:18:09,827 --> 00:18:11,133
this citadel,
it was intended

281
00:18:11,177 --> 00:18:13,266
as the high seat
of all Thrace.

282
00:18:13,309 --> 00:18:16,399
But now Thrace is divided.

283
00:18:16,443 --> 00:18:18,488
 This war has depleted
 our forces.

284
00:18:18,532 --> 00:18:20,360
 We're left with nothing
 but farmers and merchants

285
00:18:20,403 --> 00:18:22,275
 to replenish our army.

286
00:18:22,318 --> 00:18:25,060
 It takes every one of us
 to resist Rhesus.

287
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:28,107
People think he cannot be
killed by an ordinary mortal.

288
00:18:28,150 --> 00:18:29,543
Only by a god.

289
00:18:31,197 --> 00:18:33,373
 Rhesus is a sorcerer.

290
00:18:33,416 --> 00:18:36,811
  <i>His magic words confuse men,</i>
  <i>bend them to his will.</i>

291
00:18:36,854 --> 00:18:38,552
  <i>He leads an army</i>
  <i>of monsters,</i>

292
00:18:38,595 --> 00:18:40,380
  <i>half horse, half human.</i>

293
00:18:42,164 --> 00:18:43,383
 Centaurs?

294
00:18:44,035 --> 00:18:45,254
 You've actually seen them?

295
00:18:45,298 --> 00:18:46,386
 They have been seen.

296
00:18:49,519 --> 00:18:51,260
 COTYS: Come, Hercules.

297
00:18:51,304 --> 00:18:54,437
Let me show you what misery
Rhesus has brought us.

298
00:18:58,572 --> 00:19:02,576
 Every week, more refugees
 arrive seeking my protection,

299
00:19:02,619 --> 00:19:05,187
 most of them
 covered in blood,

300
00:19:05,231 --> 00:19:08,190
crippled or burnt
by Rhesus' men.

301
00:19:08,234 --> 00:19:12,586
I feared nothing could ever be
good again, till you arrived.

302
00:19:12,629 --> 00:19:14,544
 I'm just a mercenary
 fighting for gold.

303
00:19:16,503 --> 00:19:20,202
 How we view ourselves
 is of little consequence.

304
00:19:20,246 --> 00:19:22,596
 How others perceive us
 is important.

305
00:19:22,639 --> 00:19:25,512
 And your name,
 like it or not,

306
00:19:25,555 --> 00:19:27,470
is a rallying cry.

307
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:36,479
 I have seen too much reality
 to trust in legends,

308
00:19:36,523 --> 00:19:37,524
 and I am not alone.

309
00:19:38,220 --> 00:19:40,614
 Nobody has any faith anymore.

310
00:19:41,615 --> 00:19:44,139
The people need a hero.

311
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:46,228
 They need someone
 to look up to.

312
00:19:47,273 --> 00:19:50,406
My son believes in you.

313
00:19:51,364 --> 00:19:53,148
 Bring us peace and

314
00:19:55,281 --> 00:19:57,239
I will believe in you, too.

315
00:20:06,335 --> 00:20:08,250
 I'm convinced
 these are good people.

316
00:20:08,294 --> 00:20:09,904
I see. And who's
more convincing,

317
00:20:09,947 --> 00:20:11,558
 Cotys or his daughter?

318
00:20:11,601 --> 00:20:12,907
 All the gold on Earth

319
00:20:12,950 --> 00:20:14,865
 is not as convincing
 as a pair of breasts.

320
00:20:14,909 --> 00:20:17,259
 Maybe, but gold never ages.

321
00:20:17,303 --> 00:20:19,566
Which is why I got them
to double our price.

322
00:20:19,609 --> 00:20:22,612
 Double your weight in gold?
 [LAUGHS] Well done.

323
00:20:22,656 --> 00:20:24,179
Amphiaraus?

324
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:25,615
 If it be the will of Zeus.

325
00:20:25,659 --> 00:20:27,922
 Which title sounds more
 terrifying to our enemies?

326
00:20:27,965 --> 00:20:29,489
 "Hercules,
 savior of Thrace"

327
00:20:29,532 --> 00:20:31,491
 or "Hercules,
 a legend is born"?

328
00:20:31,534 --> 00:20:33,580
 Both sound
 terrifyingly boring.

329
00:20:33,623 --> 00:20:35,277
 [CHUCKLES]

330
00:20:35,321 --> 00:20:37,627
 What are we supposed to do
 with an army of farmers?

331
00:20:40,413 --> 00:20:41,892
 Train them.

332
00:20:41,936 --> 00:20:43,677
 Oh, shit. [CHUCKLES]

333
00:20:50,597 --> 00:20:53,600
 In war, there is one thing
 more important than killing.

334
00:20:54,557 --> 00:20:56,951
Surviving.

335
00:20:56,994 --> 00:21:01,303
My companions and I will
show you how to stay alive,

336
00:21:01,347 --> 00:21:04,524
 so that you may return home
 to your farms someday.

337
00:21:07,353 --> 00:21:08,354
 Autolycus.

338
00:21:09,355 --> 00:21:11,226
 Shield wall! Form!

339
00:21:20,366 --> 00:21:21,367
 [YELLING]

340
00:21:22,716 --> 00:21:24,631
 [MEN GROANING]

341
00:21:27,373 --> 00:21:28,548
 [PANTING]

342
00:21:29,636 --> 00:21:32,334
 Corpses!
 Every last one of you!

343
00:21:32,378 --> 00:21:34,684
 Because your shield wall
 was weak.

344
00:21:34,728 --> 00:21:35,772
 Dead.

345
00:21:36,773 --> 00:21:37,731
 Dead.

346
00:21:38,514 --> 00:21:39,646
 Very dead.

347
00:21:41,517 --> 00:21:43,345
 Soldier,

348
00:21:43,389 --> 00:21:46,000
 many lives depend on you.

349
00:21:46,043 --> 00:21:48,307
When attacked, lock your
feet in the ground.

350
00:21:51,353 --> 00:21:52,485
 Understand?

351
00:21:52,528 --> 00:21:53,703
 Yes, sir.

352
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:56,315
When a shield wall
is strong,

353
00:21:57,359 --> 00:22:00,362
nothing can ever
defeat it!

354
00:22:00,406 --> 00:22:02,016
 You must learn
 to work together.

355
00:22:02,059 --> 00:22:03,844
 React together.

356
00:22:03,887 --> 00:22:07,500
When you do, each individual
will become a link in a chain

357
00:22:07,543 --> 00:22:09,632
 that will be stronger
 than iron.

358
00:22:14,681 --> 00:22:16,552
I hope the enemy
has a sense of humor.

359
00:22:18,424 --> 00:22:23,037
Right. Today's lesson,
how not to stab yourselves!

360
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:26,475
 It is imperative that
 we strike now, My Lord,

361
00:22:26,519 --> 00:22:28,303
 given this opportunity.

362
00:22:28,347 --> 00:22:30,523
 COTYS: Ah! There you are!

363
00:22:30,566 --> 00:22:33,395
Hercules, my scouts
have brought news.

364
00:22:33,439 --> 00:22:34,788
 Rhesus is on the move.

365
00:22:34,831 --> 00:22:36,746
 Archers who shoot
 lightning from their bows.

366
00:22:36,790 --> 00:22:40,576
 An infantry, 4,000 strong,
 their minds bewitched.

367
00:22:40,620 --> 00:22:42,404
 Demons march with them.

368
00:22:42,448 --> 00:22:44,580
 So now
 we're fighting demons.

369
00:22:44,624 --> 00:22:48,062
 No stranger than the monsters
 I hear you faced, Hercules.

370
00:22:48,105 --> 00:22:51,370
 My Lord, Rhesus is preparing
 to attack Bessi lands.

371
00:22:51,413 --> 00:22:53,459
 He will be on them
 within six days.

372
00:22:53,502 --> 00:22:57,419
If the Bessi fall, we're next.
Unless we intercept him.

373
00:22:57,463 --> 00:23:00,596
Your men need weeks, if
not months of training
before they're ready.

374
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:04,383
 The Bessi are a fierce
 but primitive tribe.

375
00:23:04,426 --> 00:23:05,514
 If we do not protect them,

376
00:23:05,558 --> 00:23:07,603
 then there will be
 a bloodbath.

377
00:23:07,647 --> 00:23:09,475
 Face Rhesus with
 an untrained army,

378
00:23:09,518 --> 00:23:11,433
and you risk losing far
more than a single battle.

379
00:23:11,477 --> 00:23:15,437
 My Lord, Rhesus is coming.
 I vouch my life on it.

380
00:23:16,482 --> 00:23:18,745
 The longer Rhesus lives,

381
00:23:18,788 --> 00:23:21,095
 the more villages
 will be burnt

382
00:23:21,138 --> 00:23:24,098
 and the more innocents
 will be killed.

383
00:23:24,141 --> 00:23:26,883
 Assemble your men.
 We march tomorrow.

384
00:23:29,799 --> 00:23:33,586
Hercules, the gods
have offered us a gift.

385
00:23:33,629 --> 00:23:36,066
 We must not squander it.

386
00:23:36,110 --> 00:23:38,373
 Are your gods going to be
 fighting with us?

387
00:23:38,852 --> 00:23:39,679
 No.

388
00:23:40,723 --> 00:23:42,725
 The son of Zeus will.

389
00:23:50,167 --> 00:23:51,778
 [INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

390
00:23:56,522 --> 00:23:57,610
[FAINT GROWLING]

391
00:23:58,175 --> 00:23:59,699
 [WHIMPERING]

392
00:24:05,531 --> 00:24:06,706
[SNARLING]

393
00:24:19,849 --> 00:24:21,634
 Ah! [SCREAMING]

394
00:24:25,812 --> 00:24:27,553
[PANTING]

395
00:24:27,596 --> 00:24:28,728
Your mother told you to stay
away. You should listen.

396
00:24:29,816 --> 00:24:30,904
 What's wrong with him?

397
00:24:34,864 --> 00:24:36,866
 Tydeus is
 my most loyal warrior.

398
00:24:38,607 --> 00:24:40,653
 He was born in war.

399
00:24:40,696 --> 00:24:44,178
When I found him, he was
more animal than human.

400
00:24:48,225 --> 00:24:49,879
 He never speaks of
 what he saw.

401
00:24:51,228 --> 00:24:56,495
He never speaks at all.

402
00:24:58,192 --> 00:24:59,672
 Come.

403
00:24:59,715 --> 00:25:00,803
 Let's find your mother.

404
00:25:07,941 --> 00:25:11,205
When I grow up, I want to
be a great hero like you.

405
00:25:11,248 --> 00:25:12,554
 Like me?

406
00:25:12,598 --> 00:25:14,208
 No hero is
 greater than Hercules.

407
00:25:14,251 --> 00:25:16,732
 I know all your Labors.
 Like the Cretan Bull.

408
00:25:16,776 --> 00:25:18,952
You wrestled it for seven
days and seven nights.

409
00:25:18,995 --> 00:25:20,606
 Uh, that's a bit
 exaggerated.

410
00:25:20,649 --> 00:25:22,956
 And struck it 49 times
 with your club.

411
00:25:22,999 --> 00:25:24,566
 Maybe not quite that many.

412
00:25:24,610 --> 00:25:26,568
 Until it fell dead
 and Crete was saved.

413
00:25:26,612 --> 00:25:28,570
 It's my favorite Labor.

414
00:25:28,614 --> 00:25:30,485
 Also Queen Hippolyta's Belt,

415
00:25:30,529 --> 00:25:33,488
 with its buxom Amazons
 and exciting bondage.

416
00:25:34,750 --> 00:25:35,969
 Do you even know
 what that means?

417
00:25:36,012 --> 00:25:37,492
 No.

418
00:25:38,841 --> 00:25:39,886
 [LAUGHS]

419
00:25:41,844 --> 00:25:42,976
 [MAN COUGHS]

420
00:25:46,893 --> 00:25:48,634
Mother.

421
00:25:48,677 --> 00:25:50,984
 Arius. You're supposed
 to be in bed.

422
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:55,728
 Why are you in the hospice?

423
00:25:55,771 --> 00:25:58,774
My mother
saves people's lives.

424
00:25:58,818 --> 00:26:00,907
 Many of our physicians
 were killed during battle,

425
00:26:00,950 --> 00:26:03,910
so out of necessity I taught
myself the art of healing.

426
00:26:06,303 --> 00:26:08,610
 If I could be like you,
 I would protect all of Thrace

427
00:26:08,654 --> 00:26:10,220
 and no one
 would ever get hurt.

428
00:26:10,264 --> 00:26:11,570
 [CHUCKLES]

429
00:26:20,056 --> 00:26:20,883
 Here.

430
00:26:22,929 --> 00:26:25,018
 I was going to give this
 to someone else,

431
00:26:26,802 --> 00:26:28,543
 but I never got the chance.

432
00:26:30,719 --> 00:26:32,939
 Only a hero may wear this.

433
00:26:32,982 --> 00:26:35,594
But to become a hero,
you must grow strong.

434
00:26:38,945 --> 00:26:40,947
 Is this
 the Nemean Lion's tooth?

435
00:26:40,990 --> 00:26:42,949
 It is. ARIUS: Thank you.

436
00:26:44,646 --> 00:26:45,081
 Thank you.

437
00:26:45,952 --> 00:26:47,301
 Good night.

438
00:26:47,344 --> 00:26:48,955
 Good night, Hercules.

439
00:26:52,959 --> 00:26:55,788
 AMPHIARAUS: Have no fear.

440
00:26:55,831 --> 00:26:58,878
 If you fall in the service
 of a just cause,

441
00:26:58,921 --> 00:27:01,576
 your souls
 will go to Elysium,

442
00:27:01,620 --> 00:27:05,319
 where they will dwell forever
 among the shades of heroes

443
00:27:05,362 --> 00:27:06,799
 like Theseus.

444
00:27:06,842 --> 00:27:08,061
 Odysseus!

445
00:27:08,104 --> 00:27:10,324
And the great Achilles.

446
00:27:10,367 --> 00:27:12,326
 Or if you're lucky,
 you'll go to Hades,

447
00:27:12,369 --> 00:27:13,893
 where all the fun people are.

448
00:27:22,118 --> 00:27:23,946
 Iolaus.

449
00:27:23,990 --> 00:27:26,340
Your place is beside Lord
Cotys, where it's safe.

450
00:27:26,383 --> 00:27:27,820
 I've been giving it
 a lot of thought,

451
00:27:27,863 --> 00:27:29,343
and I really feel
I'm ready to fight.

452
00:27:29,386 --> 00:27:30,823
 You're a storyteller,
 not a warrior.

453
00:27:30,866 --> 00:27:32,346
 We share the same blood.

454
00:27:32,389 --> 00:27:34,783
 And I will not
 see it shed. Chariot.

455
00:27:35,741 --> 00:27:37,351
 Now. [SCOFFS]

456
00:27:44,010 --> 00:27:46,055
 Thracians,

457
00:27:46,099 --> 00:27:49,711
the shield wall is your
home. Your shelter.

458
00:27:49,755 --> 00:27:52,627
 When you sleep,
 the wall is your blanket.

459
00:27:53,759 --> 00:27:56,979
When you fight,
the wall is your armor.

460
00:27:57,023 --> 00:27:59,852
 The shield wall
 will never break formation

461
00:27:59,895 --> 00:28:02,028
 as long as there is
 breath in your body.

462
00:28:03,029 --> 00:28:05,031
 Remember these words

463
00:28:06,162 --> 00:28:08,034
and you will taste victory.

464
00:28:09,905 --> 00:28:11,124
 Move the army out! SOLDIER 1: Move out!

465
00:28:12,778 --> 00:28:13,996
 SOLDIER 2: Move out!

466
00:28:58,954 --> 00:29:00,216
 [HORSES NEIGHING]

467
00:29:19,845 --> 00:29:21,020
Halt!

468
00:29:21,063 --> 00:29:22,021
 SOLDIER 1: Halt!

469
00:29:22,499 --> 00:29:23,936
 Halt!

470
00:29:23,979 --> 00:29:26,721
 SOLDIER 2: Halt!

471
00:29:27,896 --> 00:29:29,115
 SOLDIER 4: Stop marching!

472
00:29:29,985 --> 00:29:31,030
 SOLDIER 5: Stand easy!

473
00:29:56,142 --> 00:29:58,448
 We are too late.

474
00:29:58,492 --> 00:30:01,060
 Rhesus has already
 been here.

475
00:30:04,890 --> 00:30:07,762
 Leave the chariots.
 We'll go down on foot.

476
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:36,182
 The lion and the crow
 cross a field of corpses.

477
00:30:37,966 --> 00:30:40,186
I hate being right
all the time.

478
00:30:45,931 --> 00:30:47,541
 Halt. SOLDIER 1: Halt!

479
00:30:47,584 --> 00:30:48,847
 SOLDIER 2: Halt!

480
00:30:48,890 --> 00:30:49,804
 SOLDIER 3: Halt!

481
00:30:50,631 --> 00:30:52,241
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY]

482
00:30:58,247 --> 00:30:59,248
 HERCULES:
 This head is rotting.

483
00:31:01,903 --> 00:31:02,948
 A week old, at least.

484
00:31:06,255 --> 00:31:08,214
 Yet some of these
 bodies are fresh.

485
00:31:21,227 --> 00:31:22,532
 [YELLS]

486
00:31:22,576 --> 00:31:23,969
 [YELPING]

487
00:31:24,012 --> 00:31:25,361
 IOLAUS: Uncle! [BOTH GRUNTING]

488
00:31:29,365 --> 00:31:30,279
 [SHRIEKS]

489
00:31:34,109 --> 00:31:37,156
 And we've walked into a trap.

490
00:31:44,206 --> 00:31:46,208
 Shield wall!
 Form a single square!

491
00:31:46,252 --> 00:31:47,601
Protect Lord Cotys!
Iolaus, go.

492
00:31:47,644 --> 00:31:49,168
 Shield wall!

493
00:31:59,134 --> 00:32:01,920
 We're here to help them.
 Why are they attacking?

494
00:32:01,963 --> 00:32:03,573
 This is Rhesus' doing.

495
00:32:03,617 --> 00:32:06,054
 They say his spells have
 the power to cloud minds.

496
00:32:06,098 --> 00:32:08,361
Turn comrades
against each other.

497
00:32:17,022 --> 00:32:19,154
King's guards,
around Lord Cotys!

498
00:32:28,207 --> 00:32:30,992
 Amphiaraus, do we die
 in this battle?

499
00:32:31,036 --> 00:32:34,213
 My time has not come yet.
 Not sure about yours.

500
00:32:36,258 --> 00:32:37,912
 That's comforting.

501
00:32:40,175 --> 00:32:41,350
 [YELLING]

502
00:32:46,051 --> 00:32:48,009
 I think he wants a challenge.

503
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:50,229
 [ALL CHEERING]

504
00:33:07,681 --> 00:33:09,161
Hercules' fists

505
00:33:09,204 --> 00:33:11,990
 have been dipped
 in the blood of the Hydra!

506
00:33:12,033 --> 00:33:13,469
 Lethal to anyone but him!

507
00:33:16,733 --> 00:33:17,473
 Watch!

508
00:33:21,390 --> 00:33:22,696
[YELLING]

509
00:33:26,743 --> 00:33:27,440
[CHEERING STOPS]

510
00:33:30,008 --> 00:33:31,226
 Did you see that?

511
00:33:31,270 --> 00:33:33,011
 The gods fight on our side!

512
00:33:33,054 --> 00:33:34,360
 [ALL CHEERING]

513
00:33:35,491 --> 00:33:38,973
Hercules!
Hercules! Hercules!

514
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:41,236
 ALL: [CHANTING] Hercules!
 Hercules! Hercules!

515
00:33:47,068 --> 00:33:48,026
 [YELLING]

516
00:33:49,157 --> 00:33:51,333
 [ALL YELLING]

517
00:34:00,125 --> 00:34:01,343
 Battle position!

518
00:34:11,136 --> 00:34:14,139
Lady Artemis, if I am to fall,
let me be judged not to be...

519
00:34:15,270 --> 00:34:17,403
 [YELLING CONTINUES]

520
00:34:22,538 --> 00:34:23,539
 [ALL GRUNTING]

521
00:34:48,173 --> 00:34:49,174
Stand fast!

522
00:35:05,103 --> 00:35:06,365
 SITACLES:
 Hold your positions!

523
00:35:19,856 --> 00:35:21,162
 Do not yield!

524
00:36:14,433 --> 00:36:17,175
 No retreat!
 Stay in the wall!

525
00:36:18,176 --> 00:36:20,352
Hold the lines!

526
00:36:20,395 --> 00:36:22,267
 Do not yield!

527
00:36:22,310 --> 00:36:24,269
 Defend Lord Cotys!

528
00:36:33,887 --> 00:36:34,627
 [SCREAMS]

529
00:36:48,641 --> 00:36:50,208
 SITACLES: The wall
 has been breached!

530
00:36:53,602 --> 00:36:57,563
Seal up the shield wall!
Defend Lord Cotys!

531
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,179
 Whip!

532
00:37:13,970 --> 00:37:15,450
 Hercules!

533
00:37:16,364 --> 00:37:17,452
 Bring the chariots!

534
00:37:25,460 --> 00:37:27,245
 SITACLES:
 Defend your Lord!

535
00:37:36,341 --> 00:37:37,733
 No!

536
00:37:42,999 --> 00:37:44,392
 [URGES HORSES]

537
00:38:00,016 --> 00:38:01,279
[LAUGHS]

538
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:26,652
 [YELLING]

539
00:38:38,403 --> 00:38:39,491
 [GRUNTS]

540
00:38:51,807 --> 00:38:53,287
 Advance!

541
00:38:54,070 --> 00:38:54,810
 SOLDIER: Advance!

542
00:38:58,379 --> 00:38:59,424
 [GROANS]

543
00:39:03,428 --> 00:39:04,646
 [SOLDIERS CHEERING]

544
00:39:13,612 --> 00:39:14,743
 SOLDIER: Make way!

545
00:39:26,451 --> 00:39:28,583
 Where is Rhesus?

546
00:39:39,594 --> 00:39:40,813
 [INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

547
00:39:49,604 --> 00:39:50,736
 Lord Cotys.

548
00:39:52,607 --> 00:39:55,088
We came here
to save this village,

549
00:39:55,131 --> 00:39:57,656
 but, no,
 they killed half my army.

550
00:39:58,874 --> 00:40:00,354
 Rhesus.

551
00:40:00,876 --> 00:40:02,574
 This is all his doing.

552
00:40:02,617 --> 00:40:03,705
 And yours.

553
00:40:04,140 --> 00:40:05,577
 I warned you.

554
00:40:05,620 --> 00:40:07,056
Your men are brave,
but untrained,

555
00:40:07,100 --> 00:40:08,580
 unprepared for battle.

556
00:40:08,623 --> 00:40:10,712
Give me time
to make warriors.

557
00:40:14,150 --> 00:40:15,456
 Very well.

558
00:40:18,764 --> 00:40:20,461
Cover up,

559
00:40:20,505 --> 00:40:23,377
 before your loyal army
 sees you bleed like a mortal.

560
00:40:52,188 --> 00:40:54,495
 I'm applying a salve of mint,
 chamomile and clay

561
00:40:54,539 --> 00:40:56,497
 to seal the wound.

562
00:40:56,541 --> 00:40:59,152
 This is extract of lithops
 for the pain.

563
00:40:59,195 --> 00:41:00,762
 A powerful sedative.

564
00:41:00,806 --> 00:41:02,677
 You should rest here
 after consuming it.

565
00:41:02,721 --> 00:41:04,505
 It may have
 certain side effects.

566
00:41:04,549 --> 00:41:05,419
 I don't need it.

567
00:41:06,551 --> 00:41:07,769
 Ah, forgive me, I forgot.

568
00:41:07,813 --> 00:41:10,729
 No mortal can harm Hercules.
 And, uh,

569
00:41:10,772 --> 00:41:13,775
 your lion's hide
 is indestructible?

570
00:41:15,560 --> 00:41:17,649
 Drink, son of Zeus.

571
00:41:21,217 --> 00:41:24,525
 Arius' father was the same,
 he distrusted medicines.

572
00:41:24,569 --> 00:41:25,570
 Where is he now?

573
00:41:26,788 --> 00:41:29,835
 Taken by the gods
 before my son was born.

574
00:41:29,878 --> 00:41:30,749
 I'm sorry.

575
00:41:31,924 --> 00:41:33,186
I never knew my father.

576
00:41:34,970 --> 00:41:38,713
 Well, he must have been
 very, very strong. [LAUGHS]

577
00:41:41,803 --> 00:41:43,501
 Tell me about Arius.

578
00:41:43,544 --> 00:41:46,547
 Oh. He's a good boy.

579
00:41:46,591 --> 00:41:49,550
 And someday,
 he will make a fine king.

580
00:41:49,594 --> 00:41:50,769
 Do you have any children?

581
00:41:56,905 --> 00:41:58,603
 Thank you for your care.

582
00:42:09,657 --> 00:42:10,876
 The sedative
 will help you rest.

583
00:42:45,301 --> 00:42:45,998
 [MEGARA SCREAMS]

584
00:42:46,041 --> 00:42:47,565
[PANTING]

585
00:42:50,568 --> 00:42:51,656
 [CHILDREN LAUGHING]

586
00:43:04,669 --> 00:43:05,887
 [LAUGHING CONTINUES]

587
00:43:53,631 --> 00:43:54,980
 [GROWLING]

588
00:43:57,852 --> 00:43:59,593
 No!

589
00:44:00,638 --> 00:44:01,726
[SNARLING]

590
00:44:06,731 --> 00:44:07,993
 [YELLING]

591
00:44:16,392 --> 00:44:17,698
 [PANTING]

592
00:44:39,764 --> 00:44:43,028
AMPHIARAUS: It happened
again, didn't it, hmm?

593
00:44:43,071 --> 00:44:44,856
Another vision of Cerberus,

594
00:44:44,899 --> 00:44:47,728
 the three-headed
 beast of Hades?

595
00:44:47,772 --> 00:44:50,035
 The gods show you things
 they don't share with others.

596
00:44:50,905 --> 00:44:53,038
 There's a word for that.

597
00:44:53,081 --> 00:44:54,735
 Madness.

598
00:44:54,779 --> 00:44:56,737
When we were driven
from Athens,

599
00:44:56,781 --> 00:44:59,000
 I consulted the Oracle
 of Delphi on your behalf.

600
00:44:59,044 --> 00:45:00,785
Do you remember
her prophecy?

601
00:45:01,786 --> 00:45:03,396
"Hercules must
finish the Labor

602
00:45:03,439 --> 00:45:05,093
 "that remains unfinished."

603
00:45:05,137 --> 00:45:07,966
And what is that, Hercules?

604
00:45:08,009 --> 00:45:09,881
 Confront the beast
 that haunts you.

605
00:45:09,924 --> 00:45:12,144
 Only then will you
 find peace.

606
00:45:12,187 --> 00:45:14,668
 I speak from experience.
 No matter how far you run,

607
00:45:14,712 --> 00:45:17,802
 no matter how fast you go,
 the beast will follow.

608
00:45:17,845 --> 00:45:20,108
Man cannot escape his fate.

609
00:45:36,168 --> 00:45:39,911
 Room for one more
 in your company?

610
00:45:39,954 --> 00:45:43,697
It'd be a pleasure having female
companionship for a change.

611
00:45:43,741 --> 00:45:46,439
Atalanta doesn't quite
count. No offense.

612
00:45:46,482 --> 00:45:49,790
If only your manhood was
as long as your tongue.

613
00:45:49,834 --> 00:45:51,836
 Oh, both can satisfy
 in different ways.

614
00:45:55,056 --> 00:45:57,058
 You're a famed
 storyteller, Iolaus.

615
00:45:57,102 --> 00:45:58,451
 Grace me with a story.

616
00:45:59,495 --> 00:46:01,715
 Any particular subject,
 My Lady?

617
00:46:02,672 --> 00:46:05,458
Murder of a woman
and her three children.

618
00:46:08,243 --> 00:46:11,812
 Is it true? Did Hercules
 slaughter his own family?

619
00:46:11,856 --> 00:46:14,467
 Who said so?Oh, soldiers talk.

620
00:46:14,510 --> 00:46:17,470
They say if Hercules
ever returns to Athens,

621
00:46:17,513 --> 00:46:19,080
King Eurystheus
will have him executed.

622
00:46:24,520 --> 00:46:26,479
 Hercules had
 completed his Labors

623
00:46:26,522 --> 00:46:27,828
 and returned home,
 but Hera...

624
00:46:27,872 --> 00:46:30,918
No myths. I want the truth.

625
00:46:30,962 --> 00:46:32,180
 No one knows the truth.

626
00:46:33,834 --> 00:46:34,792
 Not for sure.

627
00:46:35,575 --> 00:46:38,099
 We found Hercules alone.

628
00:46:38,143 --> 00:46:40,449
 His wife, Megara,
 the children, dead.

629
00:46:40,493 --> 00:46:42,190
 He remembers nothing.

630
00:46:42,234 --> 00:46:44,105
 Do you believe
 he is innocent?

631
00:46:45,150 --> 00:46:46,978
 We grew up together,

632
00:46:47,021 --> 00:46:48,849
 both orphans,
 trying to survive

633
00:46:48,893 --> 00:46:50,503
 in the streets of Athens.

634
00:46:50,546 --> 00:46:54,986
 We found a home in the army.
 Looked out for each other.

635
00:46:55,029 --> 00:46:59,120
 Hercules' strength
 set him apart.

636
00:46:59,164 --> 00:47:00,992
 The Kings of Athens

637
00:47:01,035 --> 00:47:02,863
would send him on all the
most dangerous missions.

638
00:47:02,907 --> 00:47:04,125
 The Twelve Labors.

639
00:47:04,169 --> 00:47:05,910
 And he took me with him.

640
00:47:06,911 --> 00:47:08,521
 Fight by his side.

641
00:47:08,564 --> 00:47:11,959
 And with each mission,
 our numbers grew.

642
00:47:12,003 --> 00:47:13,918
 Scythia, the Amazon kingdom

643
00:47:13,961 --> 00:47:16,224
 where the royal family
 had been assassinated.

644
00:47:16,268 --> 00:47:18,879
 My family was gone.
 Everyone was gone.

645
00:47:18,923 --> 00:47:21,490
 Hercules helped me
 avenge their murder.

646
00:47:21,534 --> 00:47:23,101
He became
my brother-in-arms.

647
00:47:24,319 --> 00:47:27,279
 Thebes, the city of corpses,

648
00:47:27,322 --> 00:47:29,890
 where we found
 a single child

649
00:47:29,934 --> 00:47:31,283
 still alive.

650
00:47:32,197 --> 00:47:34,286
 Hercules took Tydeus in

651
00:47:34,329 --> 00:47:37,071
when everyone else saw
nothing but a wild animal.

652
00:47:38,594 --> 00:47:39,987
 You know how
 a rumor spreads.

653
00:47:40,031 --> 00:47:41,989
 How a legend grows.

654
00:47:42,033 --> 00:47:44,818
 Hercules' deeds
 were so incredible

655
00:47:44,862 --> 00:47:47,212
they could not possibly have
been performed by a mere mortal.

656
00:47:47,952 --> 00:47:50,171
So we played along.

657
00:47:50,215 --> 00:47:53,218
 We encourage people to think
 Hercules was the son of Zeus.

658
00:47:53,261 --> 00:47:54,915
 It's good.

659
00:47:54,959 --> 00:47:56,177
 Scares the enemy.

660
00:47:56,221 --> 00:47:57,875
 Iolaus helps.

661
00:47:58,266 --> 00:47:59,354
 He talks nice.

662
00:48:01,095 --> 00:48:04,882
 And that, My Lady,
 is the truth.

663
00:48:05,230 --> 00:48:06,144
 The truth.

664
00:48:07,101 --> 00:48:08,189
[SCOFFS]

665
00:48:08,973 --> 00:48:11,192
Whatever the truth,

666
00:48:11,236 --> 00:48:14,152
the death of his loved ones
haunts Hercules.

667
00:48:14,195 --> 00:48:16,328
Only the gods can help him,

668
00:48:17,633 --> 00:48:19,157
if he listens.

669
00:48:26,251 --> 00:48:29,950
Come! Gather around, soldiers
of Thrace, and behold.

670
00:48:29,994 --> 00:48:32,953
When Hercules gives an
order, even the gods listen.

671
00:48:32,997 --> 00:48:35,086
 Zeus' master ironsmith

672
00:48:35,129 --> 00:48:37,610
using the forges
of your own citadel

673
00:48:37,653 --> 00:48:39,612
has crafted
these divine weapons

674
00:48:39,655 --> 00:48:42,180
that will make you
invincible.

675
00:48:42,223 --> 00:48:45,226
 As steel is
 hewn into shields,

676
00:48:45,270 --> 00:48:47,881
 so, too, will you be hewn
 into warriors.

677
00:48:50,666 --> 00:48:54,105
You shall carry
the shield of Hercules!

678
00:49:02,374 --> 00:49:04,158
 It's lighter.

679
00:49:04,202 --> 00:49:07,118
 Infused with the souls
 of the Stymphalian birds

680
00:49:07,161 --> 00:49:09,120
from Hercules' sixth Labor!

681
00:49:09,163 --> 00:49:12,123
 Spirits of birds?
 How does that work, exactly?

682
00:49:14,038 --> 00:49:16,040
 Well, much as
 birds take flight,

683
00:49:16,083 --> 00:49:17,302
 so, too, are these shields

684
00:49:17,345 --> 00:49:18,999
lighter than air.
It's in the fibers.

685
00:49:19,043 --> 00:49:20,348
 Here.

686
00:49:20,392 --> 00:49:23,134
 Try on the helmet
 of Hercules.

687
00:49:30,054 --> 00:49:31,969
 It covers my whole face.

688
00:49:32,012 --> 00:49:34,362
 Forged after Hercules'
 very own helmet,

689
00:49:34,406 --> 00:49:37,017
when he defeated
the demon Geryon.

690
00:49:37,061 --> 00:49:40,368
You sure it wasn't your
horseshit that frightened
Geryon to death?

691
00:49:40,412 --> 00:49:41,674
 Mmm?

692
00:49:41,717 --> 00:49:43,545
 IOLAUS: General Sitacles,

693
00:49:43,589 --> 00:49:46,418
perhaps you would care to
inspect the armor of Hercules?

694
00:49:56,384 --> 00:49:57,472
 [CHUCKLES]

695
00:50:01,737 --> 00:50:03,435
 Leather armor?

696
00:50:04,305 --> 00:50:05,306
 Mmm?

697
00:50:06,307 --> 00:50:08,222
 We will be
 skewered like pigs.

698
00:50:08,266 --> 00:50:09,963
 [SITACLES GRUNTS] [SOLDIERS GASP]

699
00:50:11,747 --> 00:50:13,271
Linothorax.

700
00:50:14,750 --> 00:50:18,102
 Hewn from the skin of
 the Erymanthian Boar.

701
00:50:18,145 --> 00:50:19,451
 It's indestructible.

702
00:50:22,236 --> 00:50:23,455
 Now, wait,
 if it's indestructible,

703
00:50:23,498 --> 00:50:25,326
 how did Hercules
 cut it off the boar?

704
00:50:27,502 --> 00:50:31,115
 He used an indestructible
 blade. [SCOFFS]

705
00:50:31,158 --> 00:50:32,377
 [SOLDIERS MURMURING]

706
00:50:47,435 --> 00:50:49,307
 SOLDIERS:
 One, two... [GRUNTS]

707
00:50:50,134 --> 00:50:53,050
 One, two... [GRUNTS]

708
00:50:53,093 --> 00:50:55,095
 One, two... [GRUNTS]

709
00:50:55,139 --> 00:50:57,228
 One, two... [GRUNTS]

710
00:50:57,793 --> 00:50:58,751
[GRUNTS]

711
00:51:00,318 --> 00:51:01,406
 Get up.

712
00:51:03,364 --> 00:51:04,365
Next!

713
00:51:07,803 --> 00:51:09,022
 [SOLDIERS GRUNTING]

714
00:51:11,807 --> 00:51:13,113
 Again!

715
00:51:13,809 --> 00:51:15,115
 Both eyes open.

716
00:51:17,248 --> 00:51:18,336
Keep practicing.

717
00:51:19,815 --> 00:51:21,121
 [GROANS]

718
00:51:21,165 --> 00:51:22,383
 Firmer grip.

719
00:51:23,254 --> 00:51:24,342
 Elbow up.

720
00:51:26,126 --> 00:51:27,127
 Good.

721
00:51:27,171 --> 00:51:28,346
 Shield wall! Form!

722
00:51:34,395 --> 00:51:35,222
 ATALANTA: Stand tall. [SOLDIER GRUNTS]

723
00:51:38,791 --> 00:51:39,444
 Excellent.

724
00:51:42,099 --> 00:51:43,796
 HERCULES: All right.[SOLDIERS APPLAUDING]

725
00:51:43,839 --> 00:51:44,536
 [ALL GRUNTING]

726
00:51:53,414 --> 00:51:54,372
 Spread out.

727
00:51:55,199 --> 00:51:56,461
 [IOLAUS GRUNTING]

728
00:52:06,471 --> 00:52:08,429
 Careful you don't
 cut yourself, boy.

729
00:52:10,344 --> 00:52:11,389
 AUTOLYCUS: Again!

730
00:52:13,347 --> 00:52:14,609
 [SOLDIERS GRUNTING]

731
00:52:18,613 --> 00:52:21,529
Rhesus is here.

732
00:52:21,573 --> 00:52:24,228
Close enough to stick a
blade between his ribs.

733
00:52:24,271 --> 00:52:26,447
 What did you see? Centaurs.

734
00:52:26,491 --> 00:52:28,232
 Half man, half horse.
 Hundreds of them.

735
00:52:29,494 --> 00:52:31,322
 He saw shadows in the night.

736
00:52:31,365 --> 00:52:33,846
 My Lord, I will go ahead
 into the Rhesus camp.

737
00:52:33,889 --> 00:52:36,240
 I will bring word
 of his plans.

738
00:52:41,158 --> 00:52:43,421
If we let them get past Mount
Asticus, Thrace will fall.

739
00:52:44,422 --> 00:52:46,293
 You want to stop Rhesus?

740
00:52:46,337 --> 00:52:48,382
We'll go through the forest and
they'll never see us coming.

741
00:52:48,426 --> 00:52:51,124
It'll slow down
our chariots. A gamble.

742
00:52:52,256 --> 00:52:53,518
I have a plan.

743
00:52:57,913 --> 00:52:59,611
 The scouts have returned.

744
00:52:59,654 --> 00:53:01,395
 Rhesus has made
 his camp in Mount Asticus,

745
00:53:01,439 --> 00:53:03,354
 72 leagues away.

746
00:53:03,397 --> 00:53:05,443
 Once these men are ready,
 we march.

747
00:53:07,358 --> 00:53:10,622
 So, have you seen
 if we win or lose?

748
00:53:10,665 --> 00:53:14,234
The gods have been annoyingly
silent on that matter.

749
00:53:14,278 --> 00:53:16,497
 What they have told me is
 that I'm soon to discover

750
00:53:16,541 --> 00:53:18,499
 if there truly is
 a heaven or a hell.

751
00:53:20,284 --> 00:53:22,242
 When will you die?

752
00:53:22,286 --> 00:53:25,593
Within a week in a place that
looks an awful lot like hell.

753
00:53:25,637 --> 00:53:29,467
 As always, the gods
 are generous with hints,

754
00:53:29,510 --> 00:53:32,209
 but cheap on specifics.
 [LAUGHS]

755
00:53:33,645 --> 00:53:35,908
 Oh, cheer up, Hercules.

756
00:53:35,951 --> 00:53:39,607
I've lived, not always
well, but long enough.

757
00:53:41,653 --> 00:53:43,698
 I'm ready for what's next.

758
00:53:49,922 --> 00:53:52,925
 Thracians, halt!

759
00:53:52,968 --> 00:53:54,274
[SOLDIERS GRUNT]

760
00:53:54,318 --> 00:53:56,276
 Shield wall! Form!

761
00:54:00,411 --> 00:54:01,629
Battle positions!

762
00:54:04,980 --> 00:54:06,417
 Tydeus?

763
00:54:10,682 --> 00:54:11,683
[YELLING]

764
00:54:12,597 --> 00:54:13,641
[SOLDIERS GRUNT]

765
00:54:52,550 --> 00:54:53,768
 There is no enemy camp.

766
00:54:55,030 --> 00:54:56,641
This is the right place.

767
00:54:59,992 --> 00:55:01,254
SOLDIER 1: Halt!

768
00:55:01,820 --> 00:55:02,777
SOLDIER 2: Halt!

769
00:55:14,702 --> 00:55:16,008
 Centaurs!

770
00:55:16,400 --> 00:55:17,705
They're real.

771
00:55:22,319 --> 00:55:24,582
 [BLOWING HORN]

772
00:55:34,635 --> 00:55:36,289
 [CENTAURS SHOUTING]

773
00:55:41,816 --> 00:55:43,557
 It seems that we're expected.

774
00:55:59,094 --> 00:56:00,574
 Centaurs?

775
00:56:15,589 --> 00:56:16,634
[EXHALES]

776
00:56:21,073 --> 00:56:22,727
 Rhesus!

777
00:56:22,770 --> 00:56:25,425
 You have come
 looking for a fight,

778
00:56:25,469 --> 00:56:26,861
and we are happy to oblige.

779
00:56:28,559 --> 00:56:31,518
 Hercules. The son of Zeus.

780
00:56:31,562 --> 00:56:33,477
 Your legend ends here.

781
00:56:33,520 --> 00:56:34,608
 HERCULES: Look at me.

782
00:56:35,783 --> 00:56:37,655
 Do I look afraid?

783
00:56:41,876 --> 00:56:44,575
 It is over, Cotys.

784
00:56:44,618 --> 00:56:48,100
 Mount Asticus on your front.
 The woods at your back.

785
00:56:48,143 --> 00:56:51,103
 And my troops outman you
 three to one.

786
00:56:51,146 --> 00:56:56,456
Surrender now and we shall
consider being merciful.

787
00:56:56,500 --> 00:56:58,632
 Men die who speak to
 My Lord in such a manner.

788
00:57:05,465 --> 00:57:06,901
 You've made your choice.

789
00:57:22,569 --> 00:57:23,570
Go!

790
00:57:35,452 --> 00:57:38,803
 In this moment,
 on this day,

791
00:57:38,846 --> 00:57:43,111
become the man
you were born to be!

792
00:57:43,155 --> 00:57:47,812
You have it within yourselves
to write your own legends!

793
00:57:47,855 --> 00:57:51,642
 Let it be to death
 or victory!

794
00:57:51,685 --> 00:57:53,731
 [SOLDIERS CHEERING]

795
00:57:56,473 --> 00:57:57,430
 Charge!

796
00:58:05,960 --> 00:58:06,874
 HERCULES: Shield wall!

797
00:58:07,571 --> 00:58:08,789
[SOLDIERS GRUNT]

798
00:58:08,833 --> 00:58:09,877
Flanks out!

799
00:58:19,234 --> 00:58:20,714
 Maybe today.

800
00:58:41,996 --> 00:58:43,607
Now!

801
00:58:45,870 --> 00:58:47,001
 [SOLDIERS GROANING]

802
00:59:02,887 --> 00:59:05,237
Watch as the Amazon uses
the arrows of Artemis...

803
00:59:05,280 --> 00:59:06,934
 Silence, boy!

804
00:59:11,765 --> 00:59:13,506
Spears forward!

805
00:59:13,550 --> 00:59:14,725
[SOLDIERS GRUNT]

806
00:59:25,649 --> 00:59:26,650
 [URGES HORSES]

807
00:59:32,307 --> 00:59:33,657
 Archers, ready!

808
00:59:34,788 --> 00:59:35,920
 Loose!

809
00:59:49,716 --> 00:59:51,588
 [BOTH SCREAM]

810
01:00:27,014 --> 01:00:27,972
 Advance!

811
01:00:37,634 --> 01:00:38,852
Set them aflame!

812
01:00:43,727 --> 01:00:44,728
 Take cover!

813
01:00:46,120 --> 01:00:47,731
 SITACLES:
 Defend Lord Cotys!

814
01:01:07,664 --> 01:01:08,969
 Maybe not.

815
01:01:09,013 --> 01:01:10,754
 Shield wall! Attack!

816
01:01:14,409 --> 01:01:15,846
 Push forward!

817
01:01:29,773 --> 01:01:31,992
 To kill a snake,
 cut off its head.

818
01:01:40,697 --> 01:01:41,915
 [URGING HORSE]

819
01:01:47,181 --> 01:01:48,922
 [SOLDIERS CHEERING]

820
01:01:48,966 --> 01:01:51,751
 Victory is yours,
 Lord Cotys!

821
01:01:51,795 --> 01:01:53,971
 It is not over yet!

822
01:02:00,064 --> 01:02:01,065
 Yeah!

823
01:02:25,916 --> 01:02:27,004
 [HORSE NEIGHING]

824
01:02:27,047 --> 01:02:28,092
 [PANTING]

825
01:02:28,135 --> 01:02:29,920
 Fucking centaurs.

826
01:02:29,963 --> 01:02:31,704
 [PANTING]

827
01:02:33,967 --> 01:02:36,056
 [ALL CHEERING]

828
01:02:36,100 --> 01:02:38,189
 ALL: [CHANTING]
 Hail, Lord Cotys!

829
01:02:38,232 --> 01:02:40,757
 Hail, Lord Cotys!

830
01:02:40,800 --> 01:02:44,021
 Hail, Lord Cotys!
 Hail, Lord Cotys!

831
01:02:44,848 --> 01:02:47,024
 Hail, Lord Cotys!

832
01:02:47,067 --> 01:02:48,721
 [SOLDIERS BOOING]

833
01:03:13,877 --> 01:03:15,139
SITACLES: Halt!

834
01:03:20,535 --> 01:03:22,102
 [SOLDIERS LAUGH]

835
01:03:22,146 --> 01:03:23,277
Get up.

836
01:03:24,539 --> 01:03:25,976
 Get up.

837
01:03:31,546 --> 01:03:33,113
[SOLDIERS LAUGH]

838
01:03:33,157 --> 01:03:35,072
 Up. Enough!

839
01:03:45,299 --> 01:03:48,999
You helped a tyrant
enslave a nation.

840
01:03:49,042 --> 01:03:51,828
All I did was stop you
from burning more villages.

841
01:03:51,871 --> 01:03:52,916
 I burned no villages.

842
01:03:53,568 --> 01:03:55,005
HERCULES: Then who did?

843
01:03:55,048 --> 01:03:57,790
Ask yourself.
If Cotys is beloved,

844
01:03:57,834 --> 01:03:59,879
why did he need to hire
mercenaries to do his
dirty work?

845
01:03:59,923 --> 01:04:01,533
 Keep moving, dog.

846
01:04:01,576 --> 01:04:04,014
 You've been fighting
 on the wrong side.

847
01:04:13,327 --> 01:04:14,807
[MUSIC PLAYING]

848
01:04:14,851 --> 01:04:15,939
 [MEN LAUGHING]

849
01:04:37,961 --> 01:04:39,876
 Where are you going?

850
01:04:39,919 --> 01:04:41,355
 I'm taking some water
 to the prisoner.

851
01:04:43,967 --> 01:04:45,185
 Sit down.

852
01:04:50,625 --> 01:04:52,062
 It's time.

853
01:04:55,935 --> 01:04:56,849
 [MUSIC STOPS]

854
01:05:02,202 --> 01:05:05,075
 Thrace is finally united.

855
01:05:07,599 --> 01:05:08,992
 One land.

856
01:05:09,644 --> 01:05:10,950
 One King.

857
01:05:12,343 --> 01:05:14,084
 One Thrace.

858
01:05:15,085 --> 01:05:16,956
 ALL: One land!

859
01:05:17,000 --> 01:05:19,263
 One King! One Thrace!

860
01:05:19,306 --> 01:05:22,309
 Thrace is not a man,
 a king, or a god!

861
01:05:22,353 --> 01:05:24,224
 Thrace is her people!

862
01:05:24,268 --> 01:05:25,269
 [GROANS]

863
01:05:25,312 --> 01:05:26,183
 [ALL LAUGHING]

864
01:05:31,405 --> 01:05:33,103
Who cares
what Rhesus claims?

865
01:05:33,146 --> 01:05:35,322
Our work is done. Let's
collect our fee and be gone.

866
01:05:47,682 --> 01:05:49,032
 Don't do anything foolish.

867
01:05:52,165 --> 01:05:53,253
 Where are you going?

868
01:05:59,346 --> 01:06:01,000
[GASPS]

869
01:06:01,044 --> 01:06:02,306
I saw pity in your eyes
for Rhesus.

870
01:06:02,349 --> 01:06:03,960
Why?

871
01:06:04,699 --> 01:06:06,266
Look at me.

872
01:06:06,310 --> 01:06:08,181
Cotys is responsible
for this war, isn't he?

873
01:06:12,446 --> 01:06:17,016
You lie very well. Clearly,
your father's daughter.

874
01:06:17,060 --> 01:06:19,149
 I didn't do it
 for my father.

875
01:06:19,192 --> 01:06:21,325
 I did it for my son.

876
01:06:21,368 --> 01:06:24,023
 If I disobeyed Cotys
 or resisted in any way,

877
01:06:24,067 --> 01:06:26,243
 Arius would be executed.

878
01:06:26,286 --> 01:06:29,333
 I did what any mother would.
 I protected my child.

879
01:06:30,464 --> 01:06:33,250
 My husband was king.

880
01:06:33,293 --> 01:06:36,035
 And Cotys poisoned him
 to take his place.

881
01:06:36,079 --> 01:06:39,169
 Rhesus fought back.
 Civil war broke out.

882
01:06:39,212 --> 01:06:41,432
 Arius is
 the legitimate king.

883
01:06:43,434 --> 01:06:45,697
 My father is old.

884
01:06:45,740 --> 01:06:49,135
 He will not live forever
 and once he is gone,

885
01:06:49,179 --> 01:06:52,182
 my son will be a good king.

886
01:06:53,226 --> 01:06:55,272
 And he will heal this land.

887
01:06:55,315 --> 01:06:56,447
 That's a dream.

888
01:06:58,318 --> 01:07:00,277
 And you can help.

889
01:07:00,320 --> 01:07:03,193
Please, when you leave
Thrace, take Arius with you.

890
01:07:03,236 --> 01:07:04,977
 Please keep him safe.

891
01:07:05,499 --> 01:07:07,327
 Find another savior.

892
01:07:08,241 --> 01:07:09,503
 SITACLES: Hercules?

893
01:07:11,505 --> 01:07:13,377
 The King commands
 your presence.

894
01:07:18,425 --> 01:07:19,731
My Lady.

895
01:07:30,785 --> 01:07:33,745
Ah, champion of Thrace!

896
01:07:33,788 --> 01:07:35,399
 Something tells me
 we're not gonna get paid.

897
01:07:36,139 --> 01:07:39,142
 You could be right. Oh, shit.

898
01:07:42,188 --> 01:07:45,148
 You wanted conquerors,
 not heroes.

899
01:07:45,191 --> 01:07:47,019
 You betrayed me, Cotys.

900
01:07:47,063 --> 01:07:50,109
 Betrayed?

901
01:07:50,153 --> 01:07:53,765
A mercenary who has long since
sold his conscience for gold

902
01:07:53,808 --> 01:07:56,507
can hardly presume
to judge his employers.

903
01:07:56,550 --> 01:07:58,465
 Let's not quibble
 about details.

904
01:08:03,470 --> 01:08:07,735
We all know your legend,
Hercules. But here is mine.

905
01:08:07,779 --> 01:08:10,521
 When I was a general
 in the army of Thrace,

906
01:08:10,564 --> 01:08:13,437
I had dreams
of ruling this kingdom.

907
01:08:13,480 --> 01:08:16,440
 But thanks to you,
 my dreams have grown.

908
01:08:16,483 --> 01:08:20,183
 I now crave an empire.

909
01:08:20,226 --> 01:08:23,360
 My thousands
 will train more thousands,

910
01:08:23,403 --> 01:08:25,101
 and they even more.

911
01:08:25,144 --> 01:08:27,277
The lessons of Hercules
will spread.

912
01:08:27,320 --> 01:08:30,106
 What you began here
 can never be stopped.

913
01:08:30,149 --> 01:08:33,587
 And if you fear
 what such an army may do,

914
01:08:35,111 --> 01:08:36,460
then lead it.

915
01:08:40,333 --> 01:08:43,815
 You want me to serve you?

916
01:08:43,858 --> 01:08:46,557
 Oh, spare me
 the moral outrage.

917
01:08:48,211 --> 01:08:49,299
 Child killer.

918
01:08:50,213 --> 01:08:52,215
 [ALL GASP]

919
01:08:52,258 --> 01:08:55,218
 Getting us all killed,
 bad idea.

920
01:08:59,352 --> 01:09:02,399
 Well, I must take this
 as a "no."

921
01:09:03,574 --> 01:09:05,097
 In that case,

922
01:09:06,577 --> 01:09:09,101
your services
are no longer required.

923
01:09:13,366 --> 01:09:16,108
 You will be paid in full.
 Bring them the gold.

924
01:09:57,541 --> 01:09:59,195
 If we hurry,

925
01:09:59,238 --> 01:10:01,371
 we could be spending
 our fortunes in Macedonia.

926
01:10:05,201 --> 01:10:06,289
 Take mine, too.

927
01:10:09,553 --> 01:10:12,860
What do you think
you're doing? Let's go.

928
01:10:12,904 --> 01:10:14,645
 There will be no more
 innocent blood on my hands.

929
01:10:14,688 --> 01:10:17,169
 I can't leave without
 setting this right.

930
01:10:18,562 --> 01:10:20,520
 Oh, I see.

931
01:10:20,564 --> 01:10:23,915
And who's gonna be paying us
for this suicidal endeavor?

932
01:10:23,958 --> 01:10:25,395
 Thrace needs our help.

933
01:10:25,438 --> 01:10:27,310
 To hell with Thrace.
 We have gold.

934
01:10:28,441 --> 01:10:29,703
 You remember
 the Black Sea.

935
01:10:29,747 --> 01:10:31,923
That beach you spoke of
is within reach.

936
01:10:31,966 --> 01:10:33,316
 Leave now, be free.

937
01:10:35,579 --> 01:10:37,581
 I would never be free.

938
01:10:40,671 --> 01:10:42,499
 In this fight, you're alone.

939
01:10:45,458 --> 01:10:47,939
 Never saw that one coming.

940
01:10:47,982 --> 01:10:49,680
How can you just walk away?
You can't just leave.

941
01:10:49,723 --> 01:10:52,422
 Why not? It's all right.

942
01:10:52,465 --> 01:10:54,424
 You've sacrificed
 your lives for me.

943
01:10:54,467 --> 01:10:55,947
 Now you can finally be free.

944
01:10:55,990 --> 01:10:58,297
 Whatever debt you feel
 you owe me is paid.

945
01:10:58,341 --> 01:10:59,646
 Debt?

946
01:11:01,300 --> 01:11:03,563
 You think we follow you
 because we owe you?

947
01:11:05,348 --> 01:11:06,479
 Look around, Hercules.

948
01:11:07,393 --> 01:11:09,439
 We're family.

949
01:11:09,482 --> 01:11:11,397
 All we have is each other.

950
01:11:12,659 --> 01:11:14,574
 We will fight for you.

951
01:11:14,618 --> 01:11:16,968
 And if it's our time,
 we will die for you.

952
01:11:17,011 --> 01:11:18,535
Because you
would die for us.

953
01:11:21,581 --> 01:11:23,496
 Take that, too.
 I have no need of it.

954
01:11:24,497 --> 01:11:25,629
 This is madness.

955
01:11:25,672 --> 01:11:27,718
 AMPHIARAUS:
 You want madness?

956
01:11:27,761 --> 01:11:30,547
 Tonight, a spear of flame
 will pierce my heart.

957
01:11:32,766 --> 01:11:35,378
Is that not the most insane
death you've ever heard of?

958
01:11:45,779 --> 01:11:48,521
 Crazy. The lot of you.

959
01:11:49,043 --> 01:11:50,393
Autolycus.

960
01:11:51,394 --> 01:11:53,744
 Iolaus. Go with Autolycus.

961
01:11:55,049 --> 01:11:56,312
I think I'll stay.

962
01:11:56,355 --> 01:11:57,530
Nephew.

963
01:11:57,574 --> 01:11:59,358
 Uncle, all I've ever done

964
01:11:59,402 --> 01:12:02,448
is tell stories of great
deeds performed by others.

965
01:12:03,797 --> 01:12:06,713
 It's time I stopped
 telling their stories.

966
01:12:06,757 --> 01:12:08,672
 Started living my own.

967
01:12:08,715 --> 01:12:11,022
Well, you may have all
completely lost your minds,

968
01:12:11,065 --> 01:12:12,415
 but not me.

969
01:12:13,807 --> 01:12:15,287
 Not me.

970
01:12:18,551 --> 01:12:19,552
 Autolycus?

971
01:12:23,426 --> 01:12:25,297
 Live like a king,
 my friend.

972
01:12:28,735 --> 01:12:29,780
 [URGES HORSES] [HORSES NEIGHING]

973
01:12:35,438 --> 01:12:36,569
 What about Cotys?

974
01:12:39,616 --> 01:12:42,053
 He paid us to save Thrace.

975
01:12:42,096 --> 01:12:43,707
 Let's not disappoint him.

976
01:12:47,363 --> 01:12:48,364
 [CREAKING]

977
01:13:12,649 --> 01:13:14,477
 SITACLES:
 Lay down your arms.

978
01:13:16,479 --> 01:13:21,353
Lay down your arms!

979
01:13:25,488 --> 01:13:26,576
 

980
01:13:37,761 --> 01:13:41,721
I invite you to join me.
You refuse.

981
01:13:41,765 --> 01:13:44,637
 I order you to leave.
 You return.

982
01:13:44,681 --> 01:13:47,379
 [GRUNTS]
 Get your hands off me.

983
01:13:49,555 --> 01:13:52,689
 I overheard her
 conspiring with Hercules.

984
01:13:52,732 --> 01:13:54,125
 They were planning
 to remove

985
01:13:54,168 --> 01:13:55,605
 the young Prince
 from your protection.

986
01:14:01,654 --> 01:14:03,134
 No. No! [ARIUS SCREAMING]

987
01:14:03,177 --> 01:14:05,484
 Let go of him!
 Don't touch him!

988
01:14:05,528 --> 01:14:06,485
 [SHOUTS]

989
01:14:08,922 --> 01:14:10,663
 Arius! No!

990
01:14:13,623 --> 01:14:15,451
[SCREAMING]

991
01:14:15,494 --> 01:14:17,148
 No, you're hurting him! No!

992
01:14:17,191 --> 01:14:19,629
 ARIUS: Hercules, no!
 Help me! Stop!

993
01:14:19,672 --> 01:14:21,718
ERGENIA: No. Arius.
[CRYING] No.

994
01:14:22,675 --> 01:14:24,460
 Arius! No![GROANING]

995
01:14:43,870 --> 01:14:45,437
 [PANTING]

996
01:14:55,229 --> 01:14:56,492
 [GROWLING]

997
01:15:03,890 --> 01:15:04,891
 [SNARLING]

998
01:15:11,724 --> 01:15:13,857
 MAN: Magnificent, aren't they?

999
01:15:15,598 --> 01:15:18,905
 An extraordinary species.
 Incredibly loyal.

1000
01:15:19,863 --> 01:15:21,865
 As long as they're fed.

1001
01:15:22,605 --> 01:15:23,649
 Remember them?

1002
01:15:23,693 --> 01:15:24,694
 Eurystheus.

1003
01:15:26,260 --> 01:15:27,958
They remember you.

1004
01:15:29,002 --> 01:15:31,614
 Confused, Hercules?

1005
01:15:32,745 --> 01:15:34,791
Kingdoms are won
with armies,

1006
01:15:34,834 --> 01:15:37,489
 but empires are made
 by alliances.

1007
01:15:38,621 --> 01:15:41,841
 King Eurystheus
 and I will now rule

1008
01:15:41,885 --> 01:15:43,756
 all of Greece.

1009
01:15:45,628 --> 01:15:46,846
 [SNARLING]

1010
01:15:49,936 --> 01:15:52,896
 Cerberus only exists
 in my mind.

1011
01:15:54,767 --> 01:15:56,639
Speak a little
louder, Hercules.

1012
01:15:58,031 --> 01:15:59,903
 I didn't quite catch that.

1013
01:16:02,558 --> 01:16:03,646
 The wolves.

1014
01:16:06,649 --> 01:16:07,911
They were there that night.

1015
01:16:08,999 --> 01:16:10,827
 <i>The wolves were there.</i>

1016
01:16:10,870 --> 01:16:12,655
  <i>You drugged me.</i>

1017
01:16:24,580 --> 01:16:25,624
 [MEGARA SCREAMING]

1018
01:16:29,323 --> 01:16:31,935
  <i>The wolves were there the</i>
  <i>night my family was murdered.</i>

1019
01:16:36,026 --> 01:16:38,550
 My men told me how
 your children screamed

1020
01:16:39,899 --> 01:16:41,988
 as my wolves gnawed
 on their bones.

1021
01:16:43,337 --> 01:16:44,774
 [GASPS]

1022
01:16:44,817 --> 01:16:47,690
 As their fangs despoiled
 your daughter's

1023
01:16:48,342 --> 01:16:49,605
 pure flesh.

1024
01:16:51,345 --> 01:16:54,914
 When the people called out
 your name louder than mine,

1025
01:16:54,958 --> 01:16:57,743
 you see, when they
 saw you as a god,

1026
01:16:57,787 --> 01:17:00,659
 how long before
 they saw you as their king?

1027
01:17:00,703 --> 01:17:02,313
 I wanted nothing!

1028
01:17:02,356 --> 01:17:05,795
Precisely! Your sin, Hercules,
was that you had no ambition!

1029
01:17:05,838 --> 01:17:07,753
I can deal with
an ambitious man!

1030
01:17:07,797 --> 01:17:09,320
He can be bought! But a
man who wants nothing

1031
01:17:09,363 --> 01:17:11,017
 has no price!

1032
01:17:13,672 --> 01:17:15,892
 Killing you would have
 turned Athens against me.

1033
01:17:16,762 --> 01:17:17,894
 I had to ruin your name.

1034
01:17:22,376 --> 01:17:23,639
 My wife!

1035
01:17:24,901 --> 01:17:26,685
 My children!

1036
01:17:26,729 --> 01:17:29,775
Well, you have our permission
to join them in death.

1037
01:17:29,819 --> 01:17:33,736
 All of you! Starting with
 my faithless daughter!

1038
01:17:34,737 --> 01:17:36,695
 ERGENIA: Let go of me!

1039
01:17:36,739 --> 01:17:39,350
 [GRUNTS] No! No! No!

1040
01:17:39,393 --> 01:17:40,830
 Unhand me!

1041
01:17:40,873 --> 01:17:42,048
 No!

1042
01:17:42,092 --> 01:17:44,094
She's your own
flesh and blood!

1043
01:17:44,137 --> 01:17:46,966
 I will raise Arius to be
 my worthy successor!

1044
01:17:47,010 --> 01:17:51,710
 You stay away from my boy!
 You monster, you bastard!

1045
01:17:51,754 --> 01:17:54,365
 You are a monster!
 You are a monster!

1046
01:17:54,408 --> 01:17:56,019
 No! [GRUNTS]

1047
01:17:56,062 --> 01:17:59,065
 ERGENIA:
 You are not a man!
 You're a demon!

1048
01:17:59,109 --> 01:18:00,371
 AMPHIARAUS: Who are you?

1049
01:18:00,414 --> 01:18:01,720
 ERGENIA: No, no, no!

1050
01:18:01,764 --> 01:18:02,852
 Are you a murderer?

1051
01:18:02,895 --> 01:18:05,724
 Damn you! I curse you!

1052
01:18:05,768 --> 01:18:07,987
Are you a mercenary who turns
his back on the innocent?

1053
01:18:08,031 --> 01:18:09,989
Stay away from my son!

1054
01:18:10,033 --> 01:18:11,730
 AMPHIARAUS: Are you
 only the legend?

1055
01:18:11,774 --> 01:18:15,125
 Or are you the truth
 behind the legend?

1056
01:18:15,168 --> 01:18:16,909
 Father, please.
 Please, please...

1057
01:18:16,953 --> 01:18:18,955
 We believe in you. [ERGENIA SOBBING]

1058
01:18:18,998 --> 01:18:20,870
 We have faith in you.

1059
01:18:20,913 --> 01:18:22,915
 Have faith in yourself.

1060
01:18:23,176 --> 01:18:24,395
[GRUNTS]

1061
01:18:24,438 --> 01:18:26,702
 Remember the man
 that you are.

1062
01:18:26,745 --> 01:18:30,009
 The gods will punish you!
 You cannot escape it!

1063
01:18:30,053 --> 01:18:32,055
 AMPHIARAUS:
 Remember the deeds
 you have performed,

1064
01:18:32,098 --> 01:18:33,143
 the Labors you have
 accomplished!

1065
01:18:34,187 --> 01:18:36,407
No. No!

1066
01:18:36,450 --> 01:18:38,148
 Stop it! Leave her alone!

1067
01:18:38,191 --> 01:18:39,758
 AMPHIARAUS: Now, tell me!

1068
01:18:39,802 --> 01:18:41,064
 [SCREAMING]

1069
01:18:41,107 --> 01:18:43,849
 Who are you?

1070
01:18:44,458 --> 01:18:47,984
I am Hercules!

1071
01:18:54,860 --> 01:18:55,948
 [GASPS]

1072
01:18:58,168 --> 01:19:00,431
 Unleash the wolves!

1073
01:19:02,172 --> 01:19:03,956
 [WOLVES SNARLING]

1074
01:19:05,131 --> 01:19:06,002
 HERCULES: Get away!

1075
01:19:06,959 --> 01:19:07,960
Ahh!

1076
01:19:15,185 --> 01:19:17,970
Three wolves should be more
than enough for one lion.

1077
01:19:19,842 --> 01:19:21,191
 [WOLF WHINES] Ahh!

1078
01:19:21,234 --> 01:19:22,714
 Hurry!

1079
01:19:26,500 --> 01:19:27,719
[GRUNTING]

1080
01:19:28,894 --> 01:19:30,026
 Hurry!Hurry!

1081
01:19:33,029 --> 01:19:34,030
 No!

1082
01:19:42,168 --> 01:19:43,039
[GRUNTING]

1083
01:19:44,475 --> 01:19:45,215
[JAW CRACKING]

1084
01:19:50,176 --> 01:19:51,221
 Ahh!

1085
01:19:53,527 --> 01:19:54,746
 [WOLF WHINES]

1086
01:20:01,187 --> 01:20:03,842
 The gods have
 revealed the truth.

1087
01:20:03,886 --> 01:20:06,497
 The final Labor
 is complete.

1088
01:20:06,540 --> 01:20:08,064
But I'm just
getting started.

1089
01:20:16,202 --> 01:20:17,769
 Doesn't take a vision to know

1090
01:20:17,813 --> 01:20:18,291
 what's waiting
 for us up there.

1091
01:20:29,172 --> 01:20:30,260
 [ALL GRUNTING]

1092
01:20:34,220 --> 01:20:35,221
 [SOLDIER SCREAMS]

1093
01:20:48,234 --> 01:20:49,235
 My time.

1094
01:20:59,245 --> 01:21:00,899
[SOLDIER SCREAMS]

1095
01:21:00,943 --> 01:21:03,206
Excuse me. That was my
moment, my fate.

1096
01:21:03,249 --> 01:21:04,555
You're welcome.

1097
01:21:05,599 --> 01:21:06,296
 [SCREAMS]

1098
01:21:17,960 --> 01:21:19,570
I'm going after Eurystheus!

1099
01:21:34,585 --> 01:21:36,065
 [GRUNTING]

1100
01:21:42,245 --> 01:21:44,595
 Hercules, listen to me.
 None of this is my fault.

1101
01:21:44,638 --> 01:21:47,076
 You see, Cotys
 poisoned my mind.

1102
01:21:47,119 --> 01:21:48,338
 Turned me against you.
 [LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]

1103
01:21:49,165 --> 01:21:50,166
 I like you.

1104
01:21:50,993 --> 01:21:52,211
 Now stop.

1105
01:21:52,255 --> 01:21:53,996
 I command you to stop!
 I'm your King!

1106
01:21:54,039 --> 01:21:55,606
You took an oath
to obey me!

1107
01:21:55,649 --> 01:21:57,913
 You swore to Zeus!

1108
01:21:57,956 --> 01:21:58,914
 Wait, wait.

1109
01:22:00,045 --> 01:22:01,612
You fight for gold.

1110
01:22:01,655 --> 01:22:04,180
 I have plenty of gold.
 Name your price.

1111
01:22:04,223 --> 01:22:06,312
 Find it in your heart
 to forgive.

1112
01:22:12,144 --> 01:22:13,885
 You want forgiveness?

1113
01:22:14,668 --> 01:22:15,321
 [GRUNTS]

1114
01:22:26,376 --> 01:22:27,203
[GROANS]

1115
01:22:30,162 --> 01:22:32,164
 Ask my family
 for forgiveness.

1116
01:22:36,168 --> 01:22:37,169
 [GRUNTS]

1117
01:22:38,954 --> 01:22:39,955
 [GRUNTING]

1118
01:22:51,053 --> 01:22:52,968
 I've never killed
 a god before.

1119
01:22:57,320 --> 01:22:58,321
 [GROANS]

1120
01:23:03,195 --> 01:23:05,067
 I really think
 I'm ready to fight now.

1121
01:23:09,680 --> 01:23:11,073
 Well done, warrior.

1122
01:23:13,466 --> 01:23:14,946
 [MEN SHOUTING]

1123
01:23:23,172 --> 01:23:25,043
 Eurystheus? Dead.

1124
01:23:25,087 --> 01:23:26,001
 We need to find Arius.

1125
01:23:26,044 --> 01:23:27,089
 HERCULES: Follow me.

1126
01:23:42,104 --> 01:23:43,714
 HERCULES: Soldiers of Thrace!

1127
01:23:43,757 --> 01:23:47,283
 You followed me in battle.
 Follow me now.

1128
01:23:47,326 --> 01:23:49,676
 Don't be fools!

1129
01:23:49,720 --> 01:23:57,380
 Hercules is mortal!
 Not a god!

1130
01:23:58,250 --> 01:24:00,122
 And I will show you.

1131
01:24:00,731 --> 01:24:02,037
 Bring him.

1132
01:24:06,128 --> 01:24:07,390
Arius!Mama!

1133
01:24:08,086 --> 01:24:09,174
No!

1134
01:24:09,218 --> 01:24:11,046
 He's your grandson!

1135
01:24:11,089 --> 01:24:13,744
 You failed to save
 your children, Hercules.

1136
01:24:13,787 --> 01:24:16,094
But you may yet save him.
 [WHIMPERS]

1137
01:24:16,138 --> 01:24:17,008
 Please, Father, no!

1138
01:24:17,443 --> 01:24:19,097
 Admit defeat!

1139
01:24:19,793 --> 01:24:22,361
 Bow to me!

1140
01:24:22,405 --> 01:24:25,103
 You have until
 the count of three!

1141
01:24:27,453 --> 01:24:28,454
One!

1142
01:24:30,282 --> 01:24:31,414
 Two!

1143
01:24:31,457 --> 01:24:32,545
 [GROANS] [SOLDIERS MURMURING]

1144
01:24:34,286 --> 01:24:36,158
Don't just stand there!
Kill someone!

1145
01:24:38,247 --> 01:24:39,378
 SOLDIER: Protect Lord Cotys.

1146
01:24:42,555 --> 01:24:44,079
 Arius, run!

1147
01:24:44,122 --> 01:24:45,080
 Mother!

1148
01:24:46,385 --> 01:24:48,126
 Get the boy!

1149
01:24:50,781 --> 01:24:52,130
 [SCREAMING]

1150
01:25:01,183 --> 01:25:02,053
 [TYDEUS YELLING]

1151
01:25:04,577 --> 01:25:05,578
[GROANS]

1152
01:25:12,803 --> 01:25:13,456
 [CONTINUES YELLING]

1153
01:25:28,210 --> 01:25:29,472
Ahh!

1154
01:25:40,874 --> 01:25:42,354
 Tydeus!

1155
01:25:46,358 --> 01:25:48,404
 Attack! [SOLDIERS YELLING]

1156
01:25:48,447 --> 01:25:49,579
 HERCULES: Hold them back!

1157
01:26:05,551 --> 01:26:07,118
 COTYS: Spears!

1158
01:26:10,252 --> 01:26:12,341
 [BOTH GROANING]

1159
01:26:12,384 --> 01:26:14,169
 Go through the fire!

1160
01:26:14,212 --> 01:26:15,431
 [SOLDIERS YELLING]

1161
01:26:19,565 --> 01:26:21,306
 Here! Help me!

1162
01:26:26,398 --> 01:26:27,486
 Easy, Tydeus.

1163
01:26:28,922 --> 01:26:30,228
[ALL YELLING]

1164
01:26:30,272 --> 01:26:31,360
 [BOTH GRUNTING]

1165
01:26:37,235 --> 01:26:37,670
 [SOLDIERS SCREAMING]

1166
01:26:55,601 --> 01:26:56,602
 H...

1167
01:26:58,648 --> 01:27:00,258
Hercules.

1168
01:27:06,699 --> 01:27:07,570
 [LAUGHS]

1169
01:27:09,311 --> 01:27:10,442
 [TYDEUS CHOKING]

1170
01:27:20,713 --> 01:27:22,237
 Lock shields!

1171
01:27:23,455 --> 01:27:24,543
 March!

1172
01:27:27,503 --> 01:27:28,634
Find peace, my brother.

1173
01:27:45,303 --> 01:27:46,957
 As you said, Hercules,

1174
01:27:47,000 --> 01:27:49,612
 there is no way
 to defeat a shield wall!

1175
01:27:50,656 --> 01:27:52,571
 There is no way out!

1176
01:27:54,356 --> 01:27:55,574
 Come out and face me!

1177
01:27:57,010 --> 01:27:58,273
[GRUNTING]

1178
01:28:03,495 --> 01:28:06,977
 You're no hero!
 You're no god!

1179
01:28:07,020 --> 01:28:09,936
You're nothing
but a mercenary!

1180
01:28:09,980 --> 01:28:12,548
 Your wife and children
 deserved to die!

1181
01:28:13,505 --> 01:28:14,593
 [YELLING]

1182
01:28:19,685 --> 01:28:20,686
 [GASPS]

1183
01:28:21,078 --> 01:28:22,384
[CONTINUES YELLING]

1184
01:28:35,048 --> 01:28:36,485
COTYS: What's he doing?

1185
01:28:36,528 --> 01:28:38,356
 Get back up there!

1186
01:28:38,400 --> 01:28:40,619
 Hercules must die!

1187
01:28:43,796 --> 01:28:45,276
 Come on!

1188
01:28:47,539 --> 01:28:50,586
 Kill the filthy bastard!

1189
01:28:53,545 --> 01:28:54,546
 [WHIMPERS]

1190
01:28:55,634 --> 01:28:56,809
[COTYS SCREAMING]

1191
01:29:27,100 --> 01:29:28,493
 [THUNDER RUMBLING]

1192
01:29:50,733 --> 01:29:53,344
 ALL: [CHANTING]
 Hercules! Hercules!

1193
01:29:53,910 --> 01:29:57,696
 Hercules! Hercules!

1194
01:29:57,740 --> 01:30:02,832
 Hercules! Hercules! Hercules!

1195
01:30:02,875 --> 01:30:06,575
 Hercules! Hercules!

1196
01:30:06,618 --> 01:30:10,405
 Hercules! Hercules!

1197
01:30:10,448 --> 01:30:13,756
 Hercules! Hercules!

1198
01:30:13,799 --> 01:30:17,107
 Hercules! Hercules!

1199
01:30:17,150 --> 01:30:20,110
 AMPHIARAUS:  <i>You want to know</i>
  <i>the truth about Hercules?</i>

1200
01:30:20,153 --> 01:30:22,678
  <i>There it is.</i>

1201
01:30:22,721 --> 01:30:26,856
  <i>To be honest,</i>
  <i>I prefer it to the legend.</i>

1202
01:30:26,899 --> 01:30:29,728
  <i>The world needs a hero</i>
  <i>they can believe in.</i>

1203
01:30:30,512 --> 01:30:34,603
 <i>Is he actually</i> 
<i>the son of Zeus?</i>

1204
01:30:34,646 --> 01:30:37,475
  <i>I don't think</i>
  <i>it really matters.</i>

1205
01:30:37,519 --> 01:30:41,131
 <i>You don't need to be</i> 
<i>a demigod to be a hero.</i>

1206
01:30:41,174 --> 01:30:44,613
 <i>You just need to believe</i> 
<i>you're a hero.</i>

1207
01:30:44,656 --> 01:30:46,745
  <i>It's what worked for him.</i>

1208
01:30:48,747 --> 01:30:53,752
 <i>But then again,</i> 
<i>what the hell do I know?</i>

1209
01:30:53,796 --> 01:30:55,885
  <i>I'm supposed to be</i>
  <i>dead by now.</i>

1210
01:30:58,844 --> 01:30:59,932
 [LIGHTNING CRASHES]
